Samburu residents have urged the government to speed up the process of issuing IDs to the youth to enable the register as voters.Maralal resident Abdillilahi Ali attributed the low turnout in the voter registration drive to lack of the crucial document.Residents say some youths applied for IDs in 2013, but they are yet to get the document. Muslim community in Samburu county chairman Ahmed Farah said the government has rejected applications for IDs from 28 Muslim youths in Maralal town.